{"id":"811951401772187648","type":"text","timestamp":1774337198,"post_url":"https://www.tumblr.com/blog/view/goodtransgirl/811951401772187648","is_reblog":true,"added_content":true,"tags":[],"reblog_ready":false,"body":"<p><a class=\"tumblr_blog\" href=\"https://www.tumblr.com/blog/view/sapphic-dice/810653685296300032\">sapphic-dice</a>:</p><blockquote><p><a class=\"tumblr_blog\" href=\"https://www.tumblr.com/blog/view/flyingturtle776/810653626125238272\">flyingturtle776</a>:</p><blockquote><p><a class=\"tumblr_blog\" href=\"https://www.tumblr.com/blog/view/sapphic-dice/810653239687118848\">sapphic-dice</a>:</p><blockquote><p>I got catcalled… but I didn’t even really notice what was happening until one of the other guys in the car of guys, as they were driving away, shouted at his friend to “STOP CATCALLING HER!”</p><p>So like, ew, but nice of that dude to tell off his friend I guess, and weirdly euphoric. Also gendered correctly lol… I guess that part makes sense at least with the catcalling. </p><p>Anyways I’m gonna eat spring rolls now.</p><p>Om nom. </p></blockquote><p>Being transfem is weird because I&rsquo;m both jealous and want to rip that guy&rsquo;s throat out</p></blockquote><p>Trust… the feeling is mutual. </p></blockquote>\n<p>I remember the first time I got catcalled.  I kept thinking, &ldquo;Do not smile.  Do not let them know how euphoric this is.  Do not encourage bad behavior&hellip;&rdquo;</p>","trail":[{"blog":{"name":"sapphic-dice","active":true,"theme":{"header_full_width":540,"header_full_height":286,"header_focus_width":390,"header_focus_height":219,"avatar_shape":"circle","background_color":"#DECBA6","body_font":"Helvetica Neue","header_bounds":"38,472,257,82","header_image":"https://64.media.tumblr.com/7ffea89de719d53c3d0af802631df95a/4e408946a718ca4f-d1/s540x286/4012131d253c21d0d656f07706c8edb61686eb97.png","header_image_focused":"https://64.media.tumblr.com/7ffea89de719d53c3d0af802631df95a/4e408946a718ca4f-d1/s2048x3072_c15185,13287,87407